The paper deals with testing independence and goodness-of-fit of structured multivariate distributions, specifically the Ising Model. This involves developing new tools for concentration of functions of the Ising model, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses sample-optimal algorithms and time efficiency, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The Ising Model is commonly used in statistical physics and probability theory, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under statistical inference (cs.SI) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
